-- UN Food-Relief Unit Buys Wheat From Glencore, Holbud for Africa
-- B y   R u d y   R u i t e n b e r g
-- 2012-01-25T10:01:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-25/un-food-relief-unit-buys-wheat-from-glencore-holbud-for-africa.html
The  United Nations ’ World Food
Programme bought $18.6 million of wheat and sorghum from
suppliers including Glencore Grain BV for shipping to the Horn
of Africa region, which is dealing with a food crisis.  The Rome-based WFP bought $10.9 million of wheat from
Glencore destined for Djibouti and Ethiopia, $3.85 million of
wheat for Kenya from Holbud Ltd. and $3.85 million of sorghum
from Nibulon SA for Kenya, Somalia and  South Sudan , according to
notifications on the agency’s website.  More than 9.6 million people in drought-affected  East
Africa  are in “desperate need” of food assistance, according
to the WFP.  The UN agency typically reports tender results with a delay
of several weeks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rudy Ruitenberg in Paris at 
